OL,3,CMinister raised concerns about
OL,4,CGovernment 'hiding' in divorce debate
OL,6,FA junior minister urged the Government
OL,7,Fnot to be "hiding" from debate during
OL,8,Fthe divisive 1995 divorce referendum
OL,9,Fcampaign, which passed by the slimmest
OL,10,Fof margins.
OL,12,FGovernment files from 30 years ago
OL,13,Fmade public by the National Archives
OL,14,Fof Ireland this weekend reveal details
OL,15,Fof government plans for the vote.
OL,17,FThe November 1995 referendum passed by
OL,18,F50.28% to 49.72%, leading to amendment
OL,19,Fof the Constitution to allow for
OL,20,Fdivorce under certain conditions.
