OL,3,CMinister raised concerns about
OL,4,CGovernment 'hiding' in divorce debate
OL,6,F"There is a possibility the
OL,7,Fsecretariat of state may raise the
OL,8,Fmatter with me directly at some stage.
OL,9,FIn the event that they do, it occurs
OL,10,Fto me that it would be useful for me
OL,11,Fto have a background brief on the
OL,12,Fissues," Mr O Broin wrote.
OL,14,FIn a follow-up letter in January 1994,
OL,15,Ffrom the department's secretary
OL,16,Fgeneral Noel Dorr to his counterpart
OL,17,Fin the Department of Equality and Law,
OL,18,FBernard McDonagh, Mr Dorr said it
OL,19,Fwould be "desirable" to give Mr O
OL,20,FBroin some guidance.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@HO]{D@JOU{D@TO]
