OL,6,F"Nevertheless, it may be desirable at
OL,7,Fthe right time, and without prejudice
OL,8,Fto positions of principle, to allow
OL,9,Fthe ambassador to brief the
OL,10,Fsecretariat of state in the Holy See
OL,11,Fon the government's proposals as this
OL,12,Fmay, indirectly, help to facilitate
OL,13,Fthe acceptance of these proposals by
OL,14,Fthe electorate here."
OL,16,FIn a separate file, Labour TD and
OL,17,Fminister of state at the Department of
OL,18,FEquality and Law Reform Mervyn Taylor
OL,19,Furged his Government colleagues to
OL,20,Fengage in open debate ahead of the
OL,21,Fvote.
